article.description: — Rafael Pinzon's 28 points helped Bryant defeat Towson 101-93 in overtime on Saturday.
article.headline: Pinzon scores 28 in Bryant's 101-93 OT victory over Towson
article.linkText: Pinzon scores 28 in Bryant's 101-93 OT victory over Towson
article.story: ELMONT, N.Y. -- — Rafael Pinzon's 28 points helped Bryant defeat Towson 101-93 in overtime on Saturday. Pinzon shot 11 for 22 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line for the Bulldogs (7-6). Doug Edert scored 20 points, shooting 3 for 8 (3 for 6 from 3-point range) and 11 of 13 from the free throw line. Daniel Rivera was 7 of 17 shooting and 2 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 16 points. Dylan Williamson finished with 18 points, four assists and three steals for the Tigers (5-6). Tyler Tejada added 16 points and seven rebounds for Towson. Messiah Jones also recorded 15 points and two steals. Towson hosts Nicholls State on Friday and Bryant hosts Drexel and Friday to. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
